==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zamouse
<hw>Za*mouse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From a native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A West African buffalo
(<spn>Bubalus brachyceros</spn>) having short horns depressed at the
base, and large ears fringed internally with three rows of long hairs.
It is destitute of a dewlap. Called also <altname>short-horned
buffalo</altname>, and <altname>bush cow</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zampogna</ent>⟦br⟧
